items.name: Crotchgate
items.description:
The $Crotchgate Scandal 

The viral controversy at the 2026 Milan-Cortina Winter Olympics: ski jumping's "Crotchgate" 

History & Origins (2025)  
Norway's top ski jumpers (including Marius Lindvik and Johann AndrÃ© Forfang) were caught cheating at the Nordic World Championships. Coaches and a technician secretly added illegal stiff stitching and extra fabric to the crotch of competition suits after they passed inspections. The lower crotch boosted aerodynamic lift for longer jumps. Coaches and the technician received 18-month bans; some athletes got shorter suspensions. FIS responded with stricter rules for 2026: advanced 3D body scans (especially the crotch area) and redesigned suits to prevent tampering.

The Recent Twist (Jan-Feb 2026)  
German tabloid Bild reported rumors that some jumpers were injecting hyaluronic acid filler into their penises before suit measurements. A temporary increase in girth would inflate 3D scan readings, allowing slightly larger suits with extra crotch fabric for more lift (potentially adding 5-6 meters to jumps). No athletes have been named or proven involved. FIS calls it a wild rumor with no evidence. WADA says they'll investigate if proof emerges. Enhanced crotch inspections are now in use at the Games.

I have no doubt that everyone has seen 
â€œCrotchgateâ€ by now, it is already being heavily memeâ€™d with tons of news coverage and social media chatter. This will only become more viral as time goes on.
